            "answer_text": "I am fed up with Indian music.JUST MAKE GOOD MUSIC. IT WILL BECOME POPULAR. DO NOT MAKE MUSIC LIKE-1) Saree ke fall sa match kiya re.Translation- The border is matched with the saree. My heart is sometimes left, sometimes caught. (Does that even make any sense in any universe?!) Tomorrow you will sing about matching t-shirts, and trousers. 2) Kadu katega toh sab mein batega.Translation- 'When pumpkin will be cut. It will be distributed'. (I almost lost hopes on Indian music). 3) NO! Crying out in pain doesn't make it classical music. 4) Hua chokra jawaan re.- This song has vulgarity at level 1000. 5) Honey singh songs-some lyrics like 'Koshish nahin karta mein but pat jaati hai khud pe khud.' Oh yeah! You have the AXE effect, don't you. And mind you every song of his has some lyrics like that.   6) Chinta ta ta chita chita. What was that?! Was it music or some music director's toddler gone wild with instruments and his wife threatened to throw him out if he didn't publish it. 7) South Indian music has improved. But there is still scope. Maybe try avoiding drum played like a tabla in almost EVERY song. Like every person with DSLR doesn't become a photographer. Every person with instruments and weird lyrics doesn't make music. For god's sake. Please I beg you let the music be music, not noise. And lyrics be good too. ",
